R100 000 is up for grabs for a hole-in-one when SWD Cricket will host their annual golf day at the Oudtshoorn Golf Club on Friday, May 28th.This big opportunity for the lucky golfer will be at the par 3 12th hole where the first player on the day who can sink the ball from the tee will walk away with the prize money.Over the years 17 players have managed a hole-in-one on this hole with the late Desmond Malgas the first to do so on 19 April 1987.Entities who are still interested in entering a four-ball can contact Zenobia Nel at 044 272 6604.